Description: Smart battery charging scheduled around grid demand
 eco-battery adjusts laptop battery charging based on electricity grid
 demand curves. It charges at demand valleys (cheap, low-carbon electricity)
 and discharges at demand peaks (expensive peaker plants), reducing grid
 stress exactly when it matters most.
 .
 This is a win-win: reduced CO2 emissions from avoided peaker plant use,
 and significantly extended battery lifespan - lithium-ion cells degrade
 much faster when kept at high state-of-charge.
 .
 Requires kernel support for battery charge threshold control or
 charge_behaviour (e.g. ThinkPad via thinkpad_acpi, ASUS via asus-nb-wmi,
 or other supported drivers). The app detects unsupported hardware on
 startup and shows a clear error.
